post_text: Thanks to all of the JC Lady Dragons for their hard work and dedication this year. This team is young but has a great deal of heart, determination and talent. I know the future is bright for this group! Next week starts a new season. The good book says that faith can move mountains. Have faith in yourself and your team and go out and play like champions! Also, thanks to the players and coaches for allowing me to call the games again this year. I have thoroughly enjoyed it! ~ Terry

post_text:
Congratulations to the players and coaches of the JC Lady Dragons on one of the most incredible turnaround seasons that could be imagined. They NEVER quit. Everyone that has been associated with this team will look back on this season with pride.

In years to come, when you walk through the halls of Junction City School and see all of the trophies in the cases, look for the 2014 State Softball Runner Up Trophy..... Think of the team that everyone said had no chance. Think of the grit and determination of this team. Think of how they never quit when they had every opportunity to settle for a mediocre season. Think of the Dragon Pride that took them all the way to the State Championship Game (and the short bus that got them there). Thank you 2014 Lady Dragons! You are all winners. On and off the field!

post_text: Three young ladies that have shown a lot of heart and leadership will play their final regular season home game tomorrow. We salute you ladies for what you have accomplished in your high school careers. You are all fighters and have helped to make this softball program one of the best in the state! Olivia Petty, Jenny Williams, Holland Risinger #LDS4LIFE!

post_text: What the El Dorado News Times failed to mention was that the Lady Dragons got out of a bases loaded 1 out jam by turning a 1, 2, 3 double play, (Bentley to Hopper to Holland Risinger), that another rally was stopped by a Risinger to Hodge double play and that Jessica Langley gunned down a runner at second from left field. All of this to go along with the two HUGE hits from Henley and Dallis!! JC fans are proud of you Ladies! Keep up the good work!!
